verses.text:
Darkness has now safely fled the hill, but the golden light shine forth,
And the lamp of God's love bright and clear, shall fill the earth;
O soul, the light of God's love bright and clear, shall fill the earth;
O soul, the light of God's love bright and clear, shall fill the earth.

O soul, the eternal day will dawn, A sweet final hope of life;
O soul, the eternal day will dawn, Peaceful, holy, bright and clear;
O soul, the eternal day will dawn, A sweet final hope of life,
O soul, the eternal day will dawn, Peaceful, holy, bright and clear.

O soul, thy Lord has come and gone, He comes that thou might have life;
O soul, thy Lord has come and gone, He comes that thou might have life;
O soul, thy Lord has come and gone, He comes that thou might have life;
O soul, thy Lord has come and gone, He comes that thou might have life.

Then rise, O soul, and catch the day, and let the light shine within;
Then rise, O soul, and catch the day, and let the light shine within;
Then rise, O soul, and catch the day, and let the light shine within;
Then rise, O soul, and catch the day, and let the light shine within.
